Error: Error: "Unable To Allocate X Amount Of RAM For Minecraft Server"

Solution: Step 1: Log in to your Pterodactyl panel and navigate to your server's dashboard.

Step 2: Click on the "File management" option under the "utilities" section.

Step 3: Open the "Start.sh" file in the root directory of your server using the built-in code editor.

Step 4: Look for the following line of code:
`java -Xms1
